<p class="">It is just as important for agricultural production that there should be cottages available for the key men on the farm as it is for the efficiency of the Coal Board, for the Police Force, for the Army. In all these, houses must be available for those who have to live near their jobs. I appeal to the hon. Gentleman to look at this with a little less prejudice and a little more common sense, and not sacrifice agricultural interests on the altar of dogma.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
